</head>
<body>
<div id="wrap" style="overflow-x: hidden; overflow-y: auto;">
	<div id="policy">
		<div id="policy_info">
			<table style="width:100%;">
				<tr align="center">
					<td colspan="2">
						COMPANY CAR POLICY<br>
						THE RESPONSIBILITIES OF THE DRIVER<br><br>
					</td>
				</tr>
			</table>
		</div>
	<p class="caption" style="padding-top: 10px"></p>
	<div class="search_area pt30 pb30">
		<table class="policy_tbl">
			<tr valign="top">
				<td width="100%" >
					1.	Immediately inform the department responsible for the automobile, observed any abnormalities in physical or mechanical structure of the vehicle, <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;such as noise, wear, lack of lighting the lanterns, leaking fluids or liquids, flat tire, smashed, bumps, etc...<br><br>
					<br>
					2.	In an accident of any kind, involving the driver and the vehicle, immediately inform the department responsible for the release of the use, <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;by phone 19 3373 0157<br><br>
					<br>
					3.	Respect and abide by the CTB – Brazilian Traffic Code, (Law 9.503 de 23 de setembro de 1997)<br><br>
					<br>
					4.	Being in possession of identity cards (foreigners should be with your passport), automobile document (located inside the glove compartment) and<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;driver’s license<br><br>
					<br>
					5.	Offences, penalties and administrative measures generated by the law, by not observing the Brazilian Traffic Code, during use, <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;is the sole responsibility of the driver to submit, as transfers of points lost any amount of fines received during its use<br><br>
					<br>
					6.	Do not remove or add items to the vehicle without the permission of the department, such as removing caps, pull fuel, servicing, add insulfilm,<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;or adhesives, etc..<br><br>
					<br>
					7.	His permission is exclusive to work, not being allowed to use personal and or family.<br><br>
					<br>
					8.	Any questions related to the vehicle should be taken with the department responsible for the vehicle.<br><br>
					<br>
				</td>
			</tr>
		</table>
	</div>
	</div>
</div>

</body>
</html>